<P>
   RUSSIA-SUB _ MOSCOW _ The latest developments on the efforts to
rescue anyone that may still be alive among the 118-member crew of
the Russian navy sub Kursk, which is sitting at the bottom of the
Barents Sea about 350 feet below
</P>
<P>
   the surface. A Norwegian dive team has joined British rescuers
at the site, and are assessing the damage and how best to get
crewmembers off the sunken vessel. Developing. (Coker, Cox News
Service)
