<HEADLINE>
BOND CALENDAR 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds: The word PLUS in parentheses has been used instead of the
symbol, which is nontransmittable to many newspaper systems.) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week is confined to
Monday's regular weekly auction of three- and six-month bills and a
two-year note being auctioned on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   By the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 6.06
percent; the six-month bill was 6.03 percent.
</P>
<P>
   In when-issued trading, the two-year note was being offered at a
price to yield 6.26 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The following taxable and tax-exempt fixed-income issues are
scheduled for pricing this week:
