<P>
   VIDEOGAMES-SHAKEOUT (San Francisco) _ Despite falling revenue
and earnings at Electronic Arts, the world's largest independent
videogame company, the mood at the company's Silicon Valley
corporate headquarters is one of great optimism. Part of the reason
is that executives believe they have emerged relatively unscathed
from a cyclical, and expected, downturn as the industry is moving
to a new generation of consoles. At the same time, executives
assert they have made key investments they say will take the
company to new levels of prominence. Whether they have succeeded
will become clearer in the next 60 days. By Matt Richtel.
