<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR MONDAY, AUGUST 21 
</HEADLINE>
   (Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Monday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-TOOTH-TECH-NYT (moved Thursday, August 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, August
17 about new technologies in orthodontics misidentified the firm
that managed the most recent round of financing for Align
Technology, which makes a clear-plastic alternative to braces. It
was Deutsche Banc Alex. Brown, not Robertson Stephens.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CENDANT-AVIS-NYT (moved Tuesday, August 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, August 15
about a bid for Avis Group Holdings by Henry Silverman, chief
executive of the CendantCorp., misstated the amount paid by Cendant
in 1999 to settle accusations of accounting fraud. It was $2.8
billion, not $2.8 million.
</P>
<P>
   BC-STEP-CHILDREN-NYT (moved Wednesday, August 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday 16 about
studies on the care of children raised in families with stepmothers
referred incorrectly in some copies to the location of Bowling
Green State University, where an author of two such studies
teaches. It is in Ohio, not Kentucky.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MIDAMERICA-AIRPORT-NYT (moved Friday, August 18)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, August 18
about the start of scheduled service at the -little-used MidAmerica
Airport near St. Louis misstated the destination of the newest Pan
Am flight there. It goes from MidAmerica to Gary, Ind., and
continues to Pittsburgh and Portsmouth, N.H., not Portland.
</P>
</TEXT>
