<HEADLINE>
THIS WEEK'S TV HIGHLIGHTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
TODAY 
Asked last week to rate his performance after two ``Monday Night
Football'' exhibition telecasts, Dennis Miller said: ``I'm getting
wood on the ball, I'm keeping the bat alive.'' So maybe that's the
problem. Someone oughtta clue him in during his last practice game
that there's !ital!football!off! going on out there. NFL: Green Bay
at Miami, Channel 7, 5 p.m. 
TUESDAY 
Some of the Angels' most-memorable moments in Fenway Park: 1)
Losing Game 6 of the 1986 American League Championship Series to
the Red Sox; 2) Losing Game 7 of the 1986 American League
Championship Series to the Red Sox. So, yeah, as far as the Angels
are concerned, go ahead and rip the landmark down before they
return next season. MLB: Angels at Boston, 4:05 p.m., Channel 9. 
WEDNESDAY 
Better than the two-hour finale of ``Survivor'' hosted by Bryant
Gumbel - will someone get too aggressive in the Aggressive In-Line
Skating men's vert competition? The X Games, ESPN2, 7 p.m.
(coverage each weekday on ESPN and ESPN2, ends Saturday on ABC at
noon). 
THURSDAY 
With 12 wins and about eight starts left, Chan Ho Park, who makes
his next scheduled appearance here, has the only real mathematical
shot on the Dodgers' staff to win 20 games. If he doesn't, it'll
mark the 10th straight year the team didn't produce a 20-game
winner - the longest drought in the franchise's 111-year history.
The last Dodger to win 20: Ramon Martinez (20-6) in 1990. MLB:
Montreal at Dodgers, 1:05 p.m., Fox Sports Net. 
FRIDAY 
That catchy phrase that Ernie Banks made famous. Let's see ...
somethin' to do with doubleheaders ... ``Let's all ...'' ... naw
... give us a few minutes here ... MLB: Dodgers at Chicago Cubs
doubleheader, 11:05 a.m., Fox Sports Net 2. 
SATURDAY 
On Aug. 26, college football draws its first breath. If the season
started any earlier, the kids from last year's class could attend.
To mark the occasion, the local department stores in Jacksonville,
Fla., offer the ``Chris Weinke Senior Citizen Discount.'' Pigskin
Classic: Brigham Young at Florida State, Channel 7, 5 p.m. 
SUNDAY 
Penn State's Joe Paterno needs seven wins this season to break the
all-time NCAA record for coaching victories. USC's Paul Hackett
could use 13 wins this season - starting with this one - to keep
the alumni off his back. Kickoff Classic: USC vs. Penn State,
Channel 7, 11:30 a.m.
